 century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Warwick","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, in origin a local name from the city in the West Midlands. The place name is probably from Old English <i>wær</i>, <i>wer</i> ‘weir, dam’ + <i>wīc</i> ‘industrial or processing site’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes of Warwick was born in 1067, in Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Thomas de Arderne in 1079, in Watford, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1130, at the age of 63."},"et":{"1067–1130":"1067–1130","1050–1100":"1050–1100","1080–1118":"1080–1118","1080":"1080","1118":"1118","1079":"1079","1067":"1067","1100":"1100","1130":"1130","1050":"1050","Watford, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Watford, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Warwick, Warwickshire, England":"Warwick, Warwickshire, England","Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom":"Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Watford, Northamptonshire, England":"Watford, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1067–1130":"1067–1130","1050–1100":"1050–1100","1080–1118":"1080–1118","1080":"1080","1118":"1118","1079":"1079","1067":"1067","1100":"1100","1130":"1130","1050":"1050","Watford, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Watford, Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Warwick, Warwickshire, England":"Warwick, Warwickshire, England","Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom":"Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Watford, Northamptonshire, England":"Watford, North